parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the trailer brake controller can cause the trailer brakes to malfunction, leading to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potential accidents, especially when towing in hilly or mountainous terrain.
symptoms: The trailer brake controller suddenly disconnects
displaying an error message on the screen
and the brake controller light on the dashboard goes off; the trailer brakes do not function during this time; the issue may resolve itself within seconds or minutes
but can recur frequently; the lights and signals on the trailer continue to work normally.
